 * An example of how to create a file sharing service, that allows
 * only registered ""superusers"" to see, upload and download files.
 * Useful for using as an extension of your intranet, for small businesses,
 * giving access to documents to their employees, of graded character, 
 * that should not fall in the hands of unauthorized personal.
 *
 * Notice though, unless you wish to have others spy on the information shared
 * this way, you will need to install and use SSL/TLS (https) on your server
 * system. Otherwise, the files sent back and forth between the client and the 
 * server becomes publicly visible for anyone able to somehow wiretap the traffic
 * to and from your server.
 *
 * The system also works as a ""WikiLeaks dropbox"", which allows users to anonymously
 * drop files, to anonymously give you access to files, without anyone being able to know
 * who was your source. This is done by changing the ""Access Role"" of the page to 
 * ""Nor restrictions"", at which point anonymous users will not be given til list of files
 * available on the server, but still able to upload files to the server. If you use this
 * feature, you should encourage your users to use ""Tor Browser"" to upload files, since
 * it is the only way to with 100% certainty facilitate for nobody being able to extort you,
 * to get access to your web server's log files, to see who accessed your service, and such 
 * be able to ""guess"" who your source might be for some piece of information.
 */


/*
